name: quark_test_framework
version: "1.0.0"
language: zig
module: quark_test_framework

description: |
  Quark Test Framework — Level 9.5: Full VSA Correctness & Symbol Binding Proofs.
  Tests every atomic operation (quark) of the Trinity symbolic AI stack.

  === PHILOSOPHY ===
  Every VSA operation is a "quark" — the smallest indivisible unit of symbolic computation.
  If any quark fails, the entire chain is compromised.
  This framework tests quarks in isolation AND composition.

  === QUARK CATEGORIES ===
  1. ARITHMETIC QUARKS: trit operations {-1, 0, +1}
     - t_add, t_mul, t_neg (balanced ternary axioms)
     - Proof: t_mul(-1, -1) = +1, t_mul(-1, 0) = 0, t_mul(+1, -1) = -1
  2. VSA QUARKS: bind, unbind, bundle, permute, similarity
     - Proof: unbind(bind(A, B), A) ~= B (self-inverse property)
     - Proof: similarity(A, A) = 1.0 (identity)
     - Proof: similarity(A, random) ~= 0.0 (quasi-orthogonality)
  3. ENCODING QUARKS: codebook encode/decode, sequence, graph triples
     - Proof: decode(encode("king")) = "king" (round-trip)
     - Proof: similarity(encode("king"), encode("queen")) > similarity(encode("king"), encode("car"))
  4. REASONING QUARKS: analogy, frame query, composition
     - Proof: king - man + woman ~= queen (analogy)
     - Proof: unbind(frame, role) ~= filler (slot access)
  5. INVARIANCE QUARKS: dimension independence, noise tolerance
     - Proof: accuracy scales with sqrt(D) (concentration of measure)
     - Proof: bundle(A, noise) still recoverable when noise < signal
  6. COMPOSITION QUARKS: multi-operation chains
     - Proof: bind(permute(A, k), B) != bind(A, B) (non-commutativity preserved)
     - Proof: bundleN converges to majority (central limit theorem in HD)

  === QUARK DAG ===
  Quarks form a directed acyclic graph of dependencies:
    arithmetic -> vsa_ops -> encoding -> reasoning -> invariance -> composition
  Failure at any level propagates upward.

  === GOLDEN CHAIN INTEGRATION ===
  Each quark test result is hashed and added to the provenance chain.
  Phase W+ verification: quark test proofs as ZK-commitments.

  Trinity Identity: phi^2 + 1/phi^2 = 3
  Sacred Formula: V = n * 3^k * pi^m * phi^p * e^q

types:
  QuarkCategory:
    enum:
      - arithmetic
      - vsa_ops
      - encoding
      - reasoning
      - invariance
      - composition

  QuarkResult:
    fields:
      name: String
      category: QuarkCategory
      passed: Bool
      expected: String
      actual: String
      tolerance: Float
      execution_time_ns: u64

  QuarkProof:
    fields:
      quark_name: String
      property: String
      dimensions_tested: List<usize>
      trials: usize
      success_rate: Float
      min_dimension_for_99: usize

  QuarkDAGNode:
    fields:
      name: String
      category: QuarkCategory
      dependencies: List<String>
      result: Option<QuarkResult>

  QuarkSuite:
    fields:
      name: String
      category: QuarkCategory
      quarks: List<QuarkDAGNode>
      passed: usize
      failed: usize
      skipped: usize

  QuarkReport:
    fields:
      suites: List<QuarkSuite>
      total_passed: usize
      total_failed: usize
      total_skipped: usize
      proofs: List<QuarkProof>
      provenance_hash: String
      execution_time_ms: u64

  DimensionSweep:
    fields:
      dimensions: List<usize>
      accuracies: List<Float>
      target_accuracy: Float
      min_dimension: usize

  NoiseToleranceResult:
    fields:
      noise_levels: List<Float>
      recovery_rates: List<Float>
      max_tolerable_noise: Float

  QuarkTestFramework:
    fields:
      allocator: Allocator
      dimension: usize
      num_trials: usize
      tolerance: Float
      dag: List<QuarkDAGNode>
      results: List<QuarkResult>
      proofs: List<QuarkProof>

behaviors:
  - name: initFramework
    given: Dimension, number of trials, tolerance threshold
    when: Creates test framework with DAG of all quark dependencies
    then: Framework ready to execute tests in topological order

  - name: runArithmeticQuarks
    given: Framework initialized
    when: Tests all balanced ternary operations exhaustively (3^2 = 9 cases per binary op)
    then: Returns QuarkSuite with pass/fail for each arithmetic axiom

  - name: runVSAQuarks
    given: Arithmetic quarks passed
    when: Tests bind self-inverse, bundle majority, permute cycle, similarity identity
    then: Returns QuarkSuite with statistical proofs over num_trials random vectors

  - name: runEncodingQuarks
    given: VSA quarks passed
    when: Tests codebook round-trip, sequence probe, graph triple encode/decode
    then: Returns QuarkSuite with encode/decode accuracy

  - name: runReasoningQuarks
    given: Encoding quarks passed
    when: Tests analogy solving (king-man+woman=queen), frame slot access, relation composition
    then: Returns QuarkSuite with reasoning accuracy and confidence scores

  - name: runInvarianceQuarks
    given: VSA quarks passed
    when: Sweeps dimensions [100, 500, 1000, 5000, 10000] measuring accuracy vs D
    then: Returns DimensionSweep proving accuracy scales with sqrt(D)

  - name: runNoiseToleranceQuarks
    given: VSA quarks passed
    when: Adds increasing noise to bound vectors, measures recovery rate
    then: Returns NoiseToleranceResult with max tolerable noise level

  - name: runCompositionQuarks
    given: All previous quarks passed
    when: Tests multi-operation chains (bind+permute, bundle+unbind, encode+reason)
    then: Returns QuarkSuite proving composition preserves properties

  - name: runFullDAG
    given: Framework initialized
    when: Executes all quark suites in topological order, skipping if dependency failed
    then: Returns QuarkReport with full results, proofs, and provenance hash

  - name: generateProvenance
    given: QuarkReport completed
    when: Hashes all results into SHA256 chain compatible with Golden Chain
    then: Returns provenance hash for Phase W+ verification

  - name: generateReport
    given: QuarkReport completed
    when: Formats results as markdown table with pass/fail, proofs, metrics
    then: Returns formatted report string for documentation

  - name: compareVersions
    given: Two QuarkReports (current vs baseline)
    when: Compares pass rates, execution times, proof strengths
    then: Returns regression/improvement analysis
